          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ", and everything shifted. You type a description of what you want, and the AI writes the code, tests it, and deploys it. Not a mockup. Not a wireframe. A real, working application.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you have ever had an app idea but lacked the time, team, or technical skills to build it, keep reading. These tips and best ways will help you squeeze every bit of value from Emergent.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What Makes Emergent Different from Other AI Tools",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Plenty of AI tools generate code snippets. Emergent generates entire applications — frontend, backend, database, deployment. All from a single text prompt.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here is what stood out when I first used it:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Full-stack output",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ": You do not get a half-baked prototype. You get a deployable app with real functionality.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Automatic testing",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ": The AI runs tests on the code it writes. Bugs get caught before you ever see them.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "One-click deployment",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ": No wrestling with hosting providers or CI/CD pipelines. Emergent handles it.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The platform has already served over 3 million users worldwide, and it is backed by Y Combinator (S24 batch). That kind of pedigree does not happen by accident.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-emergent"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you are curious about the core mechanics, this ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "step-by-step guide on how to use Emergent",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " breaks the process down beautifully.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tips to Write Prompts That Actually Work",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The quality of your app depends heavily on how you describe it. Vague prompts produce vague results. Here is how to get specific:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 1: Define the user flow, not just the feature.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Instead of \"build a task manager,\" try: \"Build a task manager where users can create projects, add tasks with due dates, drag tasks between columns (To Do, In Progress, Done), and receive email reminders 24 hours before a deadline.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 2: Mention the tech stack if you have a preference.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Emergent is flexible. You can specify React for the frontend, Node.js for the backend, or PostgreSQL for the database. The AI respects your choices.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 3: Include edge cases early.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Want user authentication? Say so. Need role-based access (admin vs. viewer)? Spell it out. The more context you provide upfront, the fewer revisions you need later.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 4: Iterate in small steps.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Start with the core feature. Get it working. Then add complexity. Emergent handles incremental updates well — you can add new pages, API endpoints, or integrations after the initial build.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l2",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/emergent-use-cases"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I used this exact approach to build a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "client dashboard in under 30 minutes",
            "marks": [
              "l2"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ". Thirty minutes. What used to take me a full sprint.",
            "marks": []
          }
